data.meta_description:
414 likes, 4 comments - oldiesandbesties on March 2, 2024: "Clint Eastwood was born on May 31, 1930, in San Francisco. He first gained recognition with the TV series "Rawhide," but his breakthrough came with Spaghetti Western films like "A Fistful of Dollars" (1964) directed by Sergio Leone. He later starred in classics such as "The Good, the Bad and the Ugly" (1966).

Eastwood's directorial career is also impressive. He achieved great success as a director with films like "Unforgiven" (1992), "Million Dollar Baby" (2004), and "Mystic River" (2003). He also directed and starred in films like "Gran Torino" (2008).
